author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Trump brushed aside the norms of international diplomacy when he targeted narcoterrorists in Venezuela, fought with European allies and bombed Iran. Trump has also played the role of peacemaker as a driving force behind the fragile Israel-Hamas peace plan and his efforts to end the Russia-Ukraine War. But have Trump’s moves actually made the U.S. any safer?

WSJ spoke with Republican Senator Lindsey Graham and the top Democrat on the Senate Foreign Relations committee to learn about how Trump’s foreign policy moves have impacted the U.S. and the world.
